 interests" or "evil"), suggesting a need to consider the ethical and moral implications of using the concept uncritically. In every instance, however, the overriding goal is to give the reader a set of practical tools to analyze the political language that surrounds all of us at this critical point in our nation's history. Witty, informative and highly readable, Collateral Language is a lexicon of political terminology and an indispensable tool for understanding the current conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aEnglish languagezUnited StatesxRhetoric. 0aRhetoricxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  a151Antonia.  a911.  aAGENTS.  aAmericas.  aBushs.  aBut.  aCELLS.  aCollateral.  aEVIL.  aEVILDOERS.  aGeorge.  aGuide.  aIts.  aLanguage.  aNewspeak.  aNovember.  aSLEEPER.  aStar.  aThe.  aThis.  aToronto.  aTyranny.  aUsers.  aWar.  aWords.  aZerbsias.  aalmost.  aappropriating.  aarticle.  abandwagon.  abeen.  abodylinklightgreenfont.  abook.  abooks.  acolor000000civilization.  acolordarkredTHINK.  acommunity.  acomplete.  aconsidered.  acould.  adeconstruct.  adespite.  adisseminating.  adouble-Newspeak.  aexplain.  aextensive.  afont.  afonttahomaarialsans.  afreedom.  afrom.  afull.  afundamentalism.  agraphics.  agreat.  ahave.  ahomeland.  ahrefhttpwwwthestarcomhttpwwwthestarcom.  aintelligence.  ajihad.  ajump.  ajustice.  akind.  alast.  alook.  amedia.  amention.  amost.  anoInstead.  anotices.  aoriginal.  aperversion.  aphrases.  apost.  apromos.  apropagandistic.  apublication.  apublicity.  aquickie.  arather.  areceived.  arhetoric.  asearch.  asecurity.  ash